{
  "texts": [
    "The study includes both strong and weak cases of human presencing.",
    "In section seven, I characterize how human presencing can be understood as the re-evoking of absent others.",
    "Before discussing the theoretical framing of human presencing, I briefly refer to two cases of human engagement in technology.",
    "These cases are highly depend on a person's past interactions with other people.",
    "As this paper focuses on how a person's past engagements with other people shape their ongoing actions and perception, human presencing allows for an exploration of how people actively engage in an online learning environment (Kreijns et al. 2021) and the role of the other people in today's AI technology (Miceli et al. 2020; Miceli & Posada 2022)."
  ]
}